alerts.description:
...FLOOD ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 430 AM PST EARLY THIS
MORNING...
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.
* WHERE...A portion of southwest California, including the following
counties, Los Angeles and Ventura.
* WHEN...Until 430 AM PST.
* IMPACTS...Heavy rainfall could trigger shallow debris flows in and
near recent wildfire burn scars. Widespread ponding of water on
area roadways and local flooding of low lying areas and
intersections was occurring across the advisory area. Mudslides
and rockslides are likely on canyon roads.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 214 AM PST, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges
indicated moderate to heavy rain across much of the advisory
area. Many locations were reporting rainfall rates of 0.20 to
0.33 inches per hour, with local rates up to one half inch
per hours.
- Moderate to occasionally heavy rain will continue to
produce minor flooding through the early morning hours.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Long Beach, Oxnard, Thousand Oaks, Simi Valley, Ventura,
Camarillo, Fillmore, Malibu, Acton, Ojai, Pasadena, Burbank,
Glendale, Chatsworth, Woodland Hills, Northridge, Encino, Van
Nuys, Agoura Hills, Santa Clarita, Hollywood and Santa
Monica.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood

...FLOOD ADVISORY WILL EXPIRE AT 615 AM PST THIS MORNING...
The Flood Advisory will expire at 615 AM PST this morning for
eastern Los Angeles.
Rainfall has ended. Small streams and normal dry washes may still be
flowing so caution is advised. Please continue to heed remaining
road closures.

...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS
AFTERNOON...
* WHAT...West winds 15 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph
expected.
* WHERE...Most coastal and valley areas in Southwest California.
* WHEN...Until 4 PM PST this afternoon.
* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 1130 PM PST THIS EVENING...
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...A portion of southwest California, including the following
county, Los Angeles.
* WHEN...Until 1130 PM PST.
* IMPACTS...Heavy rainfall could trigger shallow debris flows in and
near recent wildfire burn scars. There will be widespread ponding
of water on area roadways and local flooding of low lying areas
and intersections.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 923 PM PST, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges
indicated moderate to heavy rain. Rainfall rates were up to
one third of an inch per hour. Minor flooding is ongoing or
expected to begin shortly in the advisory area.
- Moderate to occasionally heavy rainfall will continue to
produce minor flooding through the late evening hours.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Long Beach, eastern Malibu, Acton, Alhambra, Altadena,
Pasadena, Downtown Los Angeles, Griffith Park, Whittier,
Burbank, Hollywood, Universal City, Inglewood, West Covina,
Beverly Hills, North Hollywood, Culver City, Glendora and
Torrance.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood

...FLOOD ADVISORY WILL EXPIRE AT 615 AM PST THIS MORNING...
The Flood Advisory will expire at 615 AM PST this morning for
eastern Los Angeles.
Rainfall has ended. Small streams and normal dry washes may still be
flowing so caution is advised. Please continue to heed remaining
road closures.
